      "content": "Crypto is okay for small stuff but they know how to trace ledger patterns if they have enough resources. I'm talking about significant movement. If they've already flagged my primary accounts, they'll be looking for the exact moment I switch to crypto. How do I move funds without triggering the \"unusual activity\" flags that intelligence-grade monitoring software uses to catch transitions like this?",
